channel.title: What is anti-leech and Leech?
channel.description: Hi guys i know i sound like a noob but what is anti leech and Leech????/

item.title: What is anti-leech and Leech?
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

[quote=“Ix Soulcist xI, post:2, topic:413349”]Leech: People are take a source or base and change a few things such as the name, home area, and a few teleports and then release the source, technically everything on this website is some form of a leech.

Anti-Leech: [i]An Anti-Leech is something that is used within sources or clients, this can be used to keep people from using the source unless that person founds out the code that is causing a certain area depending on what the person has added to make the server or client to not work.

Example: Adding a bracket in a random place, this will cause 100 errors and the person that downloads the source must find the misplaced bracket to find the “anti-leech”.[/i]

These are the best definitions I could think of.[/quote]
Your posts are always so sexy looking.

item.title: What is anti-leech and Leech?
item.dc:creator: @kingman002 kingman002
item.description:
@kingman002 wrote:

This isn’t RuneScape.

Leeching is where you download something and then basically do nothing or very simple stuff and then releasing it and calling it yours.

Anti-leech is where something is added in the server or client to make it not run right and if you got something with anti-leech you have to fix it.
